The 21-year-old Angolan basketball player [Bruno
Fernando](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruno_Fernando) became the first of
his country to join an NBA team, USAâ€™s professional basketball league.

On the morning of 20 June, the player was chosen for position 34 in the
[Philadelphia 76ers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philadelphia_76ers) through
the player selection system called _draft_ in the USA.

According to the Portuguese sports newspaper â€œA Bolaâ€ (The Ball), Bruno
Fernando started playing basketball at the Angolan club [Primeiro de
Agosto,](https://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basquetebol_do_Clube_Desportivo_Primeiro_de_Agosto)
and then headed to the USA at the age of 16.

Playing for the University of Maryland, Bruno had his best performance between
2018 and 2019, when he reached averages of 13.6 points, 10.6 rebounds, and 1.9
blocks.

According to Portugal newspaper [DiÃ¡rio de NotÃ­cias](https://www.dn.pt/edicao-
do-dia/24-jun-2019/interior/a-historia-de-bruno-fernando-o-bebe-gigante-
angolano-que-chegou-a-nba-11037652.html), Bruno started with mini-basketball,
then moved to the team of initiates, and later cadets, youth, and juniors, all
with the club Primeiro de Agosto in Luanda.

